    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Phila</placeName>
                <date>March 9th 67</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Well, you are a<lb/> pretty man; why do you<lb/> not answer my
                questions?<lb/> Now just read over all<lb/> my letter to
                    <placeName>Savannah</placeName> &amp; <lb/> answer all my questions<lb/>
                particularly regarding<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Falke's<add>?</add></persName> order. <persName>Mrs
                Levin's</persName><lb/> Bible had been lettered <persName>Mrs.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="underline">Nathaniel Levin</hi></persName> before your<lb/> letter
                directing otherwise was<lb/> received, so, it cannot be<lb/> altered now; you
                should<lb/> be more particular about</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><sic>about</sic> these things.</p>
            <p>Now as I regard her <persName>Moises's</persName><lb/> meditations &amp; prayers, —
                first<lb/> you directed that <persName>Burlack<add>?</add></persName><lb/> should
                send him one; this<lb/> was done; the you directed<lb/> me to send him four
                medita-<lb/>tions &amp; Prayers, but I sent<lb/> only <hi rend="underline"
                    >three</hi> of course; if he<lb/> wants another I will send<lb/> it to him. As
                regards<lb/> the book which <persName>Miss Joseph</persName> requires, I know
                nothing a-<lb/>bout it, as this I did not read<lb/> her letter through (not
                wishing<lb/> to pry into other people's<lb/> love affairs sharing enough<lb/> to do,
                to take care of <hi rend="underline">his own</hi>.)<lb/> so please let me know
                what</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>books she wishes, &amp; it shall<lb/> be sent around to <persName>Mr
                Moses</persName>.<lb/> The Occident is out at last;<lb/> some of
                    <persName>Jones</persName> machinery broke<lb/> down &amp; delayed it for a<lb/>
                day or so; Mamma &amp; I did<lb/> the work up quickly; she<lb/> pasted &amp; I
                directed &amp; the<lb/> work was all done up in<lb/> less than 2 ½ hours.</p>
            <p>We have received a letter from<lb/>
                <persName>Uncle Sam</persName>; he views the action<lb/> of Congregation the
                darkest<lb/> light &amp; seems to announce all<lb/> hope; <hi rend="underline">do
                    not mention this I</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">beg</hi>; stop at <placeName>Mobile</placeName><add>?</add> if
                poss-<lb/>ible on your <add>?</add>; at least<lb/> write to them &amp; let <hi
                    rend="underline">them know</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">where you are</hi> (<hi rend="underline">entre
                    nous<add>?</add></hi>.)<lb/> Very few books have been sold</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>since you left; <persName>Mr Hayes</persName><lb/> bought a plain prayer book
                    <persName>Mr. Gutheim</persName> has sent a check<lb/> for $82. &amp;
                    <persName>Dovale</persName> has sent $59<lb/> from <persName>Mr. De
                    Casseres</persName>; I will<lb/> acknowledge receipt of both<lb/> tomorrow — The
                girls were<lb/> here this afternoon, they go<lb/> to <persName>Levin's</persName> on
                    <date>Sunday</date>, Mamma<lb/> has purchased beautiful dress-<lb/>es for them.
                Let us know<lb/> how your health is when you<lb/> next write. Mamma has a<lb/>
                terrible cold &amp; is feeling very<lb/> miserable indeed; we are kept<lb/>
                continually busy attending to<lb/> your affairs. The girls tell us<lb/> that
                    <persName>Mr A J. Jones</persName> wrote to you<lb/> telling you not to come
                home<lb/> until you have recovered.</p>
            <p>We all send love to you &amp; hope<lb/> that you will write soon.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours, <persName role="author">E L Cozens</persName></p>
        </body>
